<h2>Photography</h2>

<ul>
<li><a href="http://sunearth.gsfc.nasa.gov/eclipse/eclipse.html" target="_blank">Eclipse Photography</a> - Without question the world expert in all things associated with solar eclipses is Fred Espanak, who works for NASA. I had the opportunity of being part of a tour led by him to the 1994 total eclipse of the sun in Bolivia. Fred's website has all the information an avid eclipse observer needs, including instructions on photographing or videotaping an eclipse. For Fred's website, click the link below.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.fredmiranda.com" target="_blank">Fred Miranda</a> - One of my favorite websites for digital photography is fredmiranda.com. Fred provides comprehensive information for anyone using high-end digital cameras, and hosts a gallery of extraordinary digital photos. He also creates and sells programs (actions he calls them) that enhance digital images.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.canadianphotographiccentre.com" target="_blank">Canadian Photographic Centre</a> - The Canadian Photographic Centre presents excellent professional photographic courses in the downtown Toronto Studio One photo studios.  I have taken over a dozen of their courses.  They are taught by first class professional photographers in fully equipped working photo studios.  I recommend them very highly.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.luminous-landscape.com" target="_blank">Luminous-Landscape</a> - The Luminous-Landscape is the website of internationally recognized landscape photographer Michael Riechmann.  It is one of the best sites for up-to-date information on photo gear (especially Canon which is what I use), as well as host to a number of very well written papers by Michael and other well-known photographers.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.onemodelplace.com/photographer_list.cfm?P_ID=59090" target="_blank">OneModelPlace</a> - OneModelPlace is a website that links photographers with models and makeup artists.  I maintain a portfolio on the site so that prospective models can check out my work.</p>
</li>
</ul>


