<h2>Woodworking</h2>					

<p>Though I don't have time to do very much of it, I enjoy woodworking. I especially enjoy working with hand tools which includes a large variety of planes, chisels, carving tools, clamping devices, marking tools and saws. I dabble in guitar building and get to work with exotic woods such as rosewood, ebony and mahogany.</p>

<p>It's hard to find high quality tools and materials. They're not the kinds of things you find at Sears or Wal-Mart. Here are the places I go to for tools and materials.</p>

<ul>
    <li><a href="http://www.leevalley.com" target="_blank">Lee Valley</a> - This is Canada's premier tool store. It sells high quality hand and garden tools. I have most of the tools in its tool catalogue. You can order online or visit any of a number of retail stores across Canada. They have their own line of tools under the "veritas" name.</li>
    <li><a href="http://www.woodcraft.com" target="_blank">Woodcraft</a> - Woodcraft is the United States' equivalent of Lee Valley. For Canadian buyers, they have a few tools not supplied by Lee Valley (probably because of the lack of demand from a smaller Canadian marketplace). An excellent selection of quality hand tools.</li>
    <li><a href="http://www.lmii.com" target="_blank">Luthiers Mercantile International</a> - Luthiers Mercantile is in California and has the best catalogue and selection of guitar woods and parts. I'm particularly fond of their "boxed sets" which provides all of the materials needed to make a guitar. They also have an excellent selection of specialty tools for the guitar builder.</li>
    <li><a href="http://www.stewmac.com" target="_blank">Stewart-MacDonald</a> - Stewart-MacDonald is a guitar supply shop in Athens, Ohio. They don't have much in the way of woods, but have a large selection of guitar part (tuners, fretting materials, hardware, pickups, etc.) and a large selection of specialty guitar building and repair tools. The company caters to luthiers who build and repair guitars of all kinds.</li>
</ul>
